<title>BRAZIL: Brazil's Proer bank plan costs 660 mln reais - paper.</title>
<headline>Brazil's Proer bank plan costs 660 mln reais - paper.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The government has loaned about 21 billion reais to banks through a program aimed at encouraging mergers and acquisitions, known as Proer, which has cost Brasilia about 660 million reais, Brazil's leading financial daily said on Thursday.</p>
<p>Gazeta Mercantil, citing a Finance Ministry report, said Brasilia loaned 20.8 billion reais between October 1995 and March 1997 to strengthen Brazil's banking sector.</p>
<p>The program has cost the government 660 million reais, corresponding to the difference in the interest rate earned on its own investments and the below market rates it charges banks in the Proer program.</p>
<p>((--John Miller, Sao Paulo newsroom, 5511 248-5414))</p>
